  "SPOTLIGHT_TOPIC": "Corporate Finance \u2014 Capital Structure",
  "SPOTLIGHT_CARD": "<div class=\"asset-card spotlight-card\"><div class=\"asset-card-header\"><div class=\"asset-left\"><div class=\"ticker-row\"><span class=\"ticker\" style=\"font-size:1.1rem\">\ud83d\udcda CFA Spotlight</span></div><div class=\"company-name\">Corporate Finance \u2014 Capital Structure</div></div></div><div class=\"spotlight-body\"><div class=\"spotlight-why\"><div class=\"spotlight-why-label\">Why This Topic?</div>Corporate Finance has not been covered in the last 5 days. Capital structure decisions appear in ~12% of CFA L1 exam questions.</div><div class=\"spotlight-cfa-box\"><div class=\"spotlight-cfa-title\">WACC Formula</div><div class=\"formula-block\">WACC = (E/V) \u00d7 Re + (D/V) \u00d7 Rd \u00d7 (1 \u2212 Tc)</div><p>Where E = equity value, D = debt value, V = E + D, Re = cost of equity, Rd = cost of debt, Tc = tax rate</p></div></div></div>",
  "FOOTER_LOG": "Day 26 \u00b7 CVX SBUX ABT LOW TGT ETH USDJPY \u00b7 Batch 5 of 101",
  "QUIZ_Q1": "<div class=\"quiz-question\" id=\"q1\"><div class=\"quiz-q-num\">Question 1 of 5 \u00b7 Equity Valuation</div><div class=\"quiz-q-text\">CVX trades at $184.22 with EPS of $6.63. What is its P/E ratio?</div><div class=\"quiz-options\"><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(1,'A','A',this)\">A) 27.8x</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(1,'B','A',this)\">B) 25.2x</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(1,'C','A',this)\">C) 30.1x</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(1,'D','A',this)\">D) 22.4x</button></div><div class=\"quiz-explanation\" id=\"exp1\"><strong>Answer: A \u2014 27.8x</strong><br>P/E = Price / EPS = $184.22 / $6.63 = 27.8x</div></div>",
  "QUIZ_Q2": "<div class=\"quiz-question\" id=\"q2\"><div class=\"quiz-q-num\">Question 2 of 5 \u00b7 Equity Valuation</div><div class=\"quiz-q-text\">Using Gordon Growth Model, what is the value of a stock paying $3 dividend growing at 5% with 10% required return?</div><div class=\"quiz-options\"><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(2,'A','B',this)\">A) $30</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(2,'B','B',this)\">B) $60</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(2,'C','B',this)\">C) $45</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(2,'D','B',this)\">D) $75</button></div><div class=\"quiz-explanation\" id=\"exp2\"><strong>Answer: B \u2014 $60</strong><br>V = D1 / (r \u2212 g) = $3.15 / (0.10 \u2212 0.05) = $60</div></div>",
  "QUIZ_Q3": "<div class=\"quiz-question\" id=\"q3\"><div class=\"quiz-q-num\">Question 3 of 5 \u00b7 Equity Valuation</div><div class=\"quiz-q-text\">TGT has P/E of 13.5x vs WMT at 35x. If TGT re-rates to 20x, what is the upside?</div><div class=\"quiz-options\"><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(3,'A','A',this)\">A) +48%</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(3,'B','A',this)\">B) +25%</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(3,'C','A',this)\">C) +60%</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(3,'D','A',this)\">D) +35%</button></div><div class=\"quiz-explanation\" id=\"exp3\"><strong>Answer: A \u2014 +48%</strong><br>Re-rating from 13.5x to 20x = 20/13.5 \u2212 1 = 48% upside</div></div>",
  "QUIZ_Q4": "<div class=\"quiz-question\" id=\"q4\"><div class=\"quiz-q-num\">Question 4 of 5 \u00b7 Corporate Finance</div><div class=\"quiz-q-text\">A company has $60M equity, $40M debt, cost of equity 12%, cost of debt 6%, tax rate 30%. What is WACC?</div><div class=\"quiz-options\"><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(4,'A','B',this)\">A) 9.0%</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(4,'B','B',this)\">B) 8.9%</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(4,'C','B',this)\">C) 10.2%</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(4,'D','B',this)\">D) 7.5%</button></div><div class=\"quiz-explanation\" id=\"exp4\"><strong>Answer: B \u2014 8.9%</strong><br>WACC = (60/100)\u00d712% + (40/100)\u00d76%\u00d7(1\u22120.30) = 7.2% + 1.68% = 8.88%</div></div>",
  "QUIZ_Q5": "<div class=\"quiz-question\" id=\"q5\"><div class=\"quiz-q-num\">Question 5 of 5 \u00b7 Derivatives</div><div class=\"quiz-q-text\">What is the max profit on a covered call with stock at $100, strike $105, premium $3?</div><div class=\"quiz-options\"><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(5,'A','C',this)\">A) $300</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(5,'B','C',this)\">B) $500</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(5,'C','C',this)\">C) $800</button><button class=\"quiz-option\" onclick=\"answerQ(5,'D','C',this)\">D) Unlimited</button></div><div class=\"quiz-explanation\" id=\"exp5\"><strong>Answer: C \u2014 $800</strong><br>Max profit = (Strike \u2212 Stock) + Premium = ($105\u2212$100) + $3 = $8 \u00d7 100 shares = $800</div></div>"
}